-- Platts to Close its Oil Pricing Window at Midday on April 5
-- B y   S h e r r y   S u
-- 2012-03-29T15:45:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/platts-to-close-its-oil-pricing-window-at-midday-on-april-5.html
Platts, the energy news and pricing
unit of McGraw-Hill Cos., will advance the closing time of its
pricing window for oil and shipping by four hours on April 5,
the day before Easter holiday in the U.K.  The assessment process for physical and derivative oil,
shipping and petrochemicals will end at 12:30 p.m. London time
on April 5, the company in a note to its subscribers today.  Argus Media, a competitor of Platts, will also bring
forward the closing time for its London-based crude assessments
to 12:30 p.m. from 4:30 p.m. on that day, the company said in an
e-mailed response.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sherry Su in London at 
